# Python Style

- `from __future__ import annotations` at top of every file
- Type hints on all function signatures and return types
- Use `dataclass` or `NamedTuple` for structured data, not raw dicts
- Prefer `pathlib.Path` over `os.path`
- f-strings for formatting, no `.format()` or `%`
- One blank line between import groups: stdlib / third-party / local
- Logger per module: `logger = logging.getLogger(__name__)`
- No `print()` — use `logger.info()` / `logger.warning()` / `logger.error()`
- Max function length ~50 lines. Break longer functions.
- No bare `except:` — always catch specific exceptions
- Use `async def` / `await` for all I/O — never blocking calls in async context
- Docstrings: only on public API functions. One line. No obvious comments.
